The Timestamp parameter not being expected for a signature version 4 request (which uses the timestamp from an HTTP header) does appear to be the cause. AWS/EC2 rejects requests with unknown parameters, so by default we do the same for compatibility. As a work around you may be able to ignore unknown parameters:

{code}
# euca-modify-property -pbootstrap.webservices.unknown_parameter_handling=ignore
{code}

If this is the problem then we should add a special case to allow (and ignore?) the "Timestamp" parameter and perhaps other signature version 2 parameters ("SignatureVersion"?)

